pageContext.claim: “They [the Russians] tried to [get close to the Trump campaign]. I know they probably tried for her campaign [Hillary Clinton’s] too.”
pageContext.analysis: There's no evidence Russians approached the Clinton campaign to offer assistance in 2016. According to the U.S. intelligence community, the House and Senate intelligence committees and special counsel Robert Mueller, Russia engaged in unprecedented interference in the 2016 U.S. presidential election to damage Clinton's chances, help Trump win and erode confidence in U.S. democracy.
